# Deprecated & Vestigial Remnants Audit

Audit of the Second Brain systems for deprecated strategies, vestigial files, and inconsistent references. **Canonical current strategy**: logs and review live under **3-Resources/**; pipeline logs use `3-Resources/<Name>-Log.md`; Errors and Backup-Log in 3-Resources; no root-level logs or review hubs required. **Why here?** Cursor-generated or machine-only files (queue, Watcher signals, setup logs) → `.technical/` (excluded from Obsidian index via Settings → Excluded files; see Vault-Layout). Cursor-side queue and technical artifacts live under `.technical/`; never place human-authored notes there.

---

## 1. Logging — root vs 3-Resources

| Item | Current / canonical | Deprecated / vestigial | Action |
|------|---------------------|------------------------|--------|
| **Ingest-Log** | `3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md` (Logs.md, log-rotate, Vault-Change-Monitor) | Root `Ingest-Log.md`; sync conflict copy at root | Remove root duplicate; keep only `3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md`. Resolve sync conflict; archive or delete conflict copy. See [[3-Resources/Archive-Prep-Checklist#3.1 — Root-level files (move or archive)]]. |
| **obsidian_log_action default** | Pipelines should pass explicit `log_path` (e.g. `3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md` per pipeline). | MCP tool descriptor default: `"Ingest-Log.md"` (root-relative) | Document in MCP-Tools.md / Pipelines that callers must pass full path `3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md` (or per-pipeline log). Optionally update MCP server default to `3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md` so omitted param is safe. |
| **mcp-setup-log.md** | Not in Logs.md or Vault-Layout as a pipeline log. | Referenced in mcp-obsidian-integration: "Append to mcp-setup-log.md or Ingest-Log.md". Used by `Logging/clone-and-install-mcp.js`. | **Vestigial**: If MCP is installed via Cursor config only, `Logging/` script and mcp-setup-log are legacy. Either (a) document mcp-setup-log as optional setup-only log and give it a path under 3-Resources (e.g. `3-Resources/mcp-setup-log.md`), or (b) remove reference from rules and keep script logging to vault root only for one-off setup. Prefer (a) for consistency. |
| **Session-Prep (Templater)** | Should append session line to the canonical ingest log. | `Templates/Session-Prep.md` and Starter-Kit copy use `logPath = "Ingest-Log.md"` (root). | Update to `3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md` in both `Templates/Session-Prep.md` and `Second-Brain-Starter-Kit/Templates/Session-Prep.md`. |
| **QuickAdd / ProcessIngestTrigger** | Should write trigger lines to canonical log. | Starter-Kit QuickAdd README and plugin report say "Ingest-Log.md" without path. | Document that trigger scripts must append to `3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md`; update any script that creates/appends to use that path. |

---

## 2. Review / inbox

| Item | Current / canonical | Deprecated / vestigial | Action |
|------|---------------------|------------------------|--------|
| **Ingest-Review** | Review is signaled via **#review-needed** in pipeline logs (`3-Resources/Ingest-Log.md`, `3-Resources/Errors.md`). MCP rule says a dedicated "Inbox Review" hub can be added later via Dataview. | Root `Ingest-Review.md`; copy in `4-Archives/Pre-Archive-Root-Cleanup/`. Some notes say "Clear #review-needed path to Ingest-Review.md". | Root file is legacy. Either (a) move to `3-Resources/Ingest-Review.md` and use as optional manual hub, or (b) archive and rely on Dataview over Ingest-Log/Errors. Update any "path to Ingest-Review" wording to "flag in Ingest-Log/Errors" or link to `3-Resources/Ingest-Review.md` if kept. |

