## 4. Hubs at root vs 3-Resources

| Item | Current / canonical | Vestigial | Action |
|------|---------------------|-----------|--------|
| **Hub placement** | Vault-Layout and Archive-Prep-Checklist: hubs can live in 3-Resources; pipeline excludes `* Hub.md` anywhere. | Checklist says "Move … Areas Hub.md, Resources Hub.md, Projects Hub.md, Resurface.md into 3-Resources/ if your layout keeps hubs there" — implies root hubs are legacy. | Canonical layout: hubs in **3-Resources/** (already true for this vault). Unit test `test_path_exclusions.py` allows both "3-Resources/Resources Hub.md" and "Projects Hub.md"; keep both for flexibility. No code change; doc only. |

---

## 5. Highlight format — legacy vs current

| Item | Current / canonical | Deprecated / vestigial | Action |
|------|---------------------|------------------------|--------|
| **Highlight output** | Inline CSS only, e.g. `<mark style="background: #A3D8FFA6;">...</mark>` (Highlightr-Color-Key, express-mini-outline). | Legacy `==text==^{Color}`; documented as deprecated; Visual Health Dashboard still counts both. | Documented; optional migration. No cleanup required except optional one-time migration of notes still using legacy format. |

